'''Shikobuchi Shrine''' (思子淵神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Takashima, Shiga|ja|高島市|12=draft}}, {{ill|Shiga Prefecture|ja|滋賀県|12=draft}}, in the Nakano district of Azugawa-chō. It was classified as a {{ill|Murasha (village shrine)|ja|村社|12=draft}} under the former shrine ranking system.

== Enshrined Deities ==
* {{ill|Shikobuchi|ja|思子淵神|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Hikohohodemi no Mikoto|ja|彦火火出見尊|12=draft}}

== Shrine Crest ==
The shrine's crest is a four-eyed rhombus (菱形四ッ目).

== History ==
Shikobuchi Shrine is said to have been founded in the first year of {{ill|Kenmu (Japan)|ja|建武|12=draft}} (1334). {{ill|Shikobuchi|ja|思子淵神|12=draft}} is a deity unique to the Azumigawa River region. It is one of the seven shrines known as "Nana Shikobuchi" (七シコブチ), all of which enshrine this deity. The Nana Shikobuchi shrines are associated with {{ill|Kappa (folklore)|ja|河童|12=draft}} legends. In {{ill|Meiji 9|ja|明治9th year|12=draft}} (1876), the shrine was officially designated as a village shrine (村社).

== Festivals ==
* Annual festival (festival) – {{ill|May 1|ja|5月1日|12=draft}}

== Sub-Shrines ==
* {{ill|Hachiman Shrine|ja|八幡神社|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Inari Shrine|ja|稲荷神社|12=draft}}

== Access ==
* From JR {{ill|Azumigawa Station|ja|安曇川駅|12=draft}}, take the {{ill|Kōjaku Bus|ja|江若バス|12=draft}} bound for Kuchiki Gakkō, get off at Nakano Bus Stop, and walk 8 minutes.

== External Links ==
* [http://www.shiga-jinjacho.jp/ycBBS/Board.cgi/02_jinja_db/db/ycDB_02jinja-pc-detail.html?mode:view=1&view:oid=1380 Shikobuchi Shrine] (Shiga Prefecture Shrine Association)

