== Shrine Crest ==
The shrine's crest is a four-eyed rhombus (菱形四ッ目).

== History ==
Shikobuchi Shrine is said to have been founded in the first year of {{ill|Kenmu (Japan)|ja|建武|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kenmu (Japan)|qq=}} (1334). {{ill|Shikobuchi|ja|思子淵神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikobuchi|qq=}} is a deity unique to the Azumigawa River region. It is one of the seven shrines known as "Nana Shikobuchi" (七シコブチ), all of which enshrine this deity. The Nana Shikobuchi shrines are associated with {{ill|Kappa (folklore)|ja|河童|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kappa (folklore)|qq=}} legends. In {{ill|Meiji 9|ja|明治9th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji 9|qq=}} (1876), the shrine was officially designated as a village shrine (村社).

== Festivals ==
* Annual festival (festival) – {{ill|May 1|ja|5月1日|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May 1|qq=}}

