'''Shikobuchi Shrine''' (思子淵神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in [[:en:Takashima, Shiga|Takashima, Shiga]], [[:en:Shiga Prefecture|Shiga Prefecture]], in the Nakano district of Azugawa-chō. It was classified as a {{ill|Murasha (village shrine)|ja|村社|1=Son-sha|qid=Q134917284}}{{efn|Former shrine rank|lt=Son-sha|1=modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Murasha (village shrine)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q712534}} under the former shrine Ranking system.

== Enshrined Deities ==
* {{ill|Shikobuchi|ja|思子淵神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikobuchi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}
* {{ill|Hoori|lt=Hoori|lt=Hikohohodemi no Mikoto|ja|彦火火出見尊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hikohohodemi no Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ホオリ|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ホオリ}}

== Shrine Crest ==
The shrine's crest is a four-eyed rhombus (菱形四ッ目).

== History ==
Shikobuchi Shrine is said to have been founded in the first year of [[:en:Jianwu|Kenmu (Japan)]] (1334). {{ill|Shikobuchi|ja|思子淵神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikobuchi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} is a deity unique to the Azumigawa River region. It is one of the seven shrines known as "Nana Shikobuchi" (七シコブチ), all of which enshrine this deity. The Nana Shikobuchi shrines are associated with [[:en:Kappa (folklore)|Kappa (folklore)]] legends. In [[:en:1876|Meiji 9]] (1876), the shrine was officially designated as a village shrine (村社).

== Festivals ==
* Annual festival (festival) – [[:en:May 1|May 1]]

== Sub-Shrines ==
* {{ill|Hachiman shrine|lt=Hachiman shrine|lt=Hachiman Shrine|ja|八幡神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 八幡宮|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 八幡宮}}
* [[:en:Inari shrine|Inari Shrine]]

== Access ==
* From JR [[:en:Adogawa Station|Azumigawa Station]], take the {{ill|Kōjaku Bus|ja|江若バス|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōjaku Bus|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 江若交通|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 江若交通|1=Kojak Bus|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11551295}} bound for Kuchiki Gakkō, get off at Nakano Bus Stop, and walk 8 minutes.

